"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-olympics-2024-cycling-emma-finucane-b1174716.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Emma Finucane: remember the name.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 278, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 245, \"end\": 249, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999907492861403, \"rank\": 9.245628366532346e-06, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old from Carmarthen begins on Monday in relative obscurity, but could end the week as one of the stars of these Games - and not solely from a British perspective.\", \"from\": 280, \"to\": 454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 301, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmarthen\", \"score\": 0.9999639432519404, \"rank\": 3.6040476384580296e-05, \"text\": \"Carmarthen\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmarthen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carmarthen\"}, {\"begin\": 434, \"end\": 441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8325799076810546, \"rank\": 0.19565002311157528, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quietly, understatedly, she has become the powerhouse of global cycle sprinting and is aiming to emulate Britain's cycling knights Sir Chris Hoy and Sir Jason Kenny, both of whom will be present at the Sain-Quentin-en-Yvelines velodrome this week, in winning triple sprint gold at a single Games.\", \"from\": 456, \"to\": 752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 561, \"end\": 568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9977096628406946, \"rank\": 0.0022955565998459887, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 591, \"end\": 600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chris Hoy\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chris_Hoy\"}, {\"begin\": 609, \"end\": 620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jason Kenny\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jason_Kenny\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chance one for the new golden girl of the track comes in the team sprint tonight, with her predecessor as golden girl, Dame Laura Kenny, saying: \\\"I am picking Emma Finucane to become a triple Olympic champion in the women's team sprint, the individual sprint and the keirin.\\\"\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 1029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 913, \"end\": 917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999907492861403, \"rank\": 9.245628366532346e-06, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kenny has GB winning as many as eight golds on the track in the coming days, which would surpass the record seven achieved at London 2012 and the six at the subsequent two Olympics.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1157, \"end\": 1168, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999979459062, \"rank\": 2.053982501037843e-09, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hoy believes that five golds are a more realistic target and that \\\"the women sprint squad will be the stars\\\".\", \"from\": 1214, \"to\": 1323, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Of Finucane, he said: \\\"Emma will be feeling the pressure to a certain degree, but I would not be surprised if she wins all three.\", \"from\": 1325, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1348, \"end\": 1352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9999907492861403, \"rank\": 9.245628366532346e-06, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"People might not know her now, but they will know who she is after the Games.\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1532, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She will probably be the superstar of the team, and the reality is she has the potential to do four more Games after this one.\\\"\", \"from\": 1534, \"to\": 1662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The width of the Paris velodrome - wider than most, London included - ought to play to the strengths of the bigger riders, like Finucane's team-mate Sophie Capewell, who also ought to get more of an aerodynamic advantage from the new skinsuits.\", \"from\": 1664, \"to\": 1908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1716, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999042092941, \"rank\": 9.193844212143694e-08, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1813, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"score\": 0.999997246383526, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sophie Capewell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Capewell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the third member of GB's women's sprint operation, Katy Marchant, is also in the medal mix.\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 2004, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1933, \"end\": 1935, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9783241097042519, \"rank\": 0.022156139944383778, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1964, \"end\": 1977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katy Marchant\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katy_Marchant\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's sprint squad lack quite the same strength, such is the dominance of the Dutch, but Kenny is tipping Jack Carlin for keirin gold.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2088, \"end\": 2093, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.613853271635085, \"rank\": 0.3738221026781218, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2116, \"end\": 2120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.9355877372950565, \"rank\": 0.06875069636856806, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 2121, \"end\": 2127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"score\": 0.9999991029876059, \"rank\": 8.970133174947069e-07, \"text\": \"Carlin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlin_Motorsport\"}, {\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.5044085938793452e-51, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}, {\"begin\": 2139, \"end\": 2143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"score\": 0.9998740593622947, \"rank\": 0.00012592481893602936, \"text\": \"gold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Finucane's rival to be the superstar of the track from a British perspective looked set to be Katie Archibald, but she broke her leg in a freak accident after tripping in her garden and misses Paris.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2345, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2203, \"end\": 2210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.8325799076810546, \"rank\": 0.19565002311157528, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 2240, \"end\": 2255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Archibald\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Archibald\"}, {\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 3.207464645364862e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And yet the team pursuit line-up will most likely either win gold or silver behind New Zealand, a race that is too close to call.\", \"from\": 2347, \"to\": 2476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2430, \"end\": 2441, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9986144441271839, \"rank\": 0.0011640085910876751, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the men's pursuit line-up should also be in the mix for the top spot on the podium, despite one of the line-up, Dan Bigham, suffering a crash in practice at the velodrome this week.\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Keely Hodgkinson reveals Grand Slam Track decision and 2025 ambitions  Incredible days out and trips for autumn and winter  Ethan Hayter is a prime candidate for omnium gold and will likely be in contention in the madison with Ollie Wood.\", \"from\": 2665, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2796, \"end\": 2812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Keely Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keely_Hodgkinson\"}, {\"begin\": 2920, \"end\": 2932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ethan Hayter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethan_Hayter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But attention from today onwards looks likely to rest firmly on Finucane, who is not unaware of the expectation, at least within British Cycling circles.\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3189, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3165, \"end\": 3180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"British Cycling\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Cycling\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not want to deny that I'd love to win gold,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3251, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But it's going to be hard.\", \"from\": 3252, \"to\": 3279, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as I do everything right, then everything is possible, whether that's gold or not.\", \"from\": 3280, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It will be what it will be.\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3398, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just want to make everyone proud.\\\"\", \"from\": 3399, \"to\": 3435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs